INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_wih3700','letter','1780-07-12','Newport','RI','US','William','Heath','','George','Washington','','individual','','I arrived here the last night, and this morning had the honor of congratulating Monsieur le Compte De Rochambeau, and Monsieur le Chevalier De Ternay, on their safe arrival in this harbour.','ltr_wih3700.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_wih3701','letter','1780-07-16','Newport','RI','US','William','Heath','','George','Washington','','individual','','The French troops are landed, and encamped in a fine situation, to the south-east of the town, and extend nearly across the Island.','ltr_wih3701.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_wih3702','letter','1780-07-21','Newport','RI','US','William','Heath','','George','Washington','','individual','','This afternoon, fifteen or sixteen British ships of war have made their appearance off this harbour, to the eastward of Block Island. More than half of them, I think, are ships of the line.','ltr_wih3702.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_wih3703','letter','1780-07-25','Newport','RI','US','William','Heath','','George','Washington','','individual','','Their intention, undoubtedly, is to block up the squadron under the command of Monsieur De Ternay, intercept the expected second division of our allies, cut off all supplies by water','ltr_wih3703.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_wih3704','letter','1780-07-25','Newport','RI','US','William','Heath','','George','Washington','','individual','','This afternoon the intelligence, contained in the inclosed, came to hand; upon which General Rochambeau immediately made a requisition for two thousand militia.','ltr_wih3704.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_wih3705','letter','1780-07-26','Newport','RI','US','William','Heath','','George','Washington','','individual','','By a variety of intelligence, from various quarters (all which agree) the enemy intend to make an attempt on the fleet and army of our great and good ally at this place.','ltr_wih3705.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_wih3706','letter','1781-01-06','West Point','NY','US','William','Heath','','George','Washington','','individual','','As to burning the houses at Morrisania, although they are a nest for the nefarious enemy, yet, as many of them belong to persons friendly to our cause, who have been obliged to abandon their habitations, it may not only be impolitic but injurious to do it.','ltr_wih3706.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_wih3707','letter','1781-05-15','Hartford','CT','US','William','Heath','','George','Washington','','individual','','I arrived here yesterday afternoon, found the General Assembly sitting, and presented your letter to Governor Trumbull, together with a representation, containing the spirit of my instructions.','ltr_wih3707.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_wih3708','letter','1780-07-31','Newport','RI','US','William','Heath','','George','Washington','','individual','','The Count wishes to detain the three months men a few days, to secure the pass at Howland\'s Ferry.','ltr_wih3708.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
